-- Security Workers to Strike at German Airports Today, Union Says
-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 2012-06-19T05:11:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-19/security-workers-to-strike-at-german-airports-today-union-says.html
Private security workers plan to
hold a two-hour strike today at several German airports,
including,  Frankfurt , over working conditions and wages, the
union ver.di said in a statement today.  The strikes are expected this morning at airports in
Frankfurt, Dusseldorf, Hamburg, Bremen and Hanover, the union
said. Passengers may see disruptions at security gates.  Ver.di is negotiating a new wage agreement and the next
meeting is planned for July 27.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in Frankfurt at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 